This paper focuses on analyzing the characteristics of real-world app crashes and improving testing and analysis tools for mobile apps. This falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also involves evaluating bug detection techniques and reviewing fixes, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The implementation of dynamic testing and exception localization tools could also fall under systems and control (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
